  "content": "# never use crypto randomUUID or Math random in reducers\n\nForbidden in reducer code:\n- `crypto.randomUUID()`\n- `Math.random()`\n- `Date.now()`\n- `new Date()`\n- Any external API calls or side effects\n- Any async functions\n\nThese are all non-deterministic. Since [[reducer purity requires all dynamic values from action input]], every value that could vary between executions must come from the operation's input schema.\n\nThe event-sourcing model replays operations to reconstruct state. If a reducer generates different values on replay, the resulting state diverges from the original, and document hashes no longer match.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[reducer patterns]]",
